'''Salarin the twisted''' is a [[chaos druid]] found at the end of the [[Yanille Agility Dungeon]]. Reaching his cave requires level 67 [[Agility]]; this can be boosted from as low as 62 with a [[summer pie]]. Additionally, players will need to bring a blade to cut the [[Web|webs]] near the dungeon entrance.

Salarin is one of the two [[NPCs]] that drop the [[sinister key]] on death, alongside the [[Chaos Fanatic]]. This key opens the [[Sinister chest]], located nearby, which rewards the player with a guaranteed noted drop of nine grimy [[herbs]] (see below), including a [[Grimy torstol|torstol]]. The key is dropped at a rate of 7.8%, making him a common target for low-level [[Ironman Mode|ironmen]] who can't yet grow the herbs.

Salarin can only be damaged by [[Strike spells]], [[ring of recoil]] damage, and [[dynamite(p)]]. He will treat Strike spells as Bolt spells, which means [[Wind Strike]] has the same maximum hit as your highest unlocked Bolt spell.

